➡️  For enterprise customers, it's unwieldy for us to be manually involved each time. *The ideal is for us to chart a product path to allowing generic deployments.* That can either be a configuration file produced by us at the point of initial onboarding of an enterprise customer, and then used for all of their apps within our platform, or a *place within the product for the customer to give us a configuration file and hookups into their cloud accounts.*

{panel:bgColor=#eae6ff}
Using Github Actions, which (if we choose to support it) is easier than Bicep or Terraform for a cross-enterprise deploy solution.
{panel}

----

So potentially Github Actions for both CI/CD and Infra Deployment? That may be possible. We will spend some time investigating some methods of fully automating it.

----

I am sharing a few more questions and feature requests that came up from last week's demo to NBC’s engineering teams.  They work on a number of very prominent apps, including Peacock. Although we demoed Studio, they were primarily asking about how the platform-devops workflow works, which is new.

* First, customers wanted to know how the intended deploy & review workflow will work to avoid pushing straight to production.
* Second, customer wanted to know how they can hook in their own automations for Github and Github actions, and how to link our system against specific branches to allow for their own internal review workflows.

