{panel}

# Find Python OpenAI SDK
# Connect to ChatGPT API
# Enable customers to send prompts to API via FE, and allow Crowdbotics to send hidden prompts on the BE
# Protect API Endpoints
## Freely exposing our endpoints could incur extra costs, and could potentially allow customers to access ChatGPT through our system for free, rather than paying for their own account.
## Our API should definitely not accept a prompt that is send directly to the ChatGPT API.
## Additionally, we should have some protections in place to prevent excessive usage charges.
# Look into “Session ID”s, i.e. storing data so as to not have to send new requests unnecessarily. 

The payload is

{noformat}export type ChatGPTPayload = {
  model: string;
  messages: Message[],
}

export type Message = {
  role: Role;
  content: string;
  name?: string;
};

export type Role = 'user' | 'system' | 'assistant';{noformat}

