Right now, if the user attempts data binding as {{{User.name}}} we generate a {{useSelector}} call as {{const User = useSelector(state => state.User)}}; 

The name of the slice is indeed the model name, in this case, Users, not _User - i.e. they are all in plural form_. Additionally, all connectors generated by the system has a specific structure that all of the data stored in an array called {{entities}} . So the {{useSelector}} call should probably be {{const { entities: Users } = useSelector(state => state.Users)}}. This way we preserve the original name of the model referenced, but get the actual value we need.

Unit tests must be added to make sure the functionality behaves as expected.

